text:
Is there a way to add "subfields" to blogs that you can use outside the blog template. Besides the default "name" and "description" etc...
I know you can you add modules to blog post pages to have extra information and fields on the specific blog pages. But if i have a section on another page (like the Home page or About page) that lists out all the "posts" I would like to have more than just the default fields that come with the posts.
For Example
```{{ blog_recent_posts("default", 5) }}

{% set rec_posts = blog_recent_posts("default", 5) %}

{% for rec_post in rec_posts %}
&lt;div&gt;
    &lt;!-- Default Name field --&gt;
    &lt;div class="post-title"&gt;{{ rec_post.name }}&lt;/div&gt; 

    &lt;!-- Hypothetical added fields --&gt;
    &lt;div&gt;{{ rec_post.subtitle }}&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div&gt;{{ rec_post.extra_field_added_here }}&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
{% endfor %}```
